  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD044862",
      "title": "SART3 is a Novel Rme2s Reader studied by tandem MS",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Arginine methylation is a ubiquitous post-translational modification involved in many biological processes such as transcription, cell signaling and RNA splicing. Tudor domains by far are the major effector domain family for arginine methylation mark recognition. Here we characterize SART3 as a novel selective reader for symmetric dimethylarginine (Rme2s) marks. SART3 harbors a series of HAT (Half-a-TPR) repeats that are aromatic-rich, and it is this region that binds Rme2s motifs. An analysis of the reported structure of the HAT repeats of SART3 identified a putative aromatic cage that potentially \u201cread\u201d the Rme2s-modified motifs, and the key aromatic residues required for Rme2s recognition were identified. We further confirm that this Rme2s reader ability is important for SART3-mediated RNA splicing. Together, our studies revealed that the evolutionarily conserved SART3 HAT domain was a novel reader of Rme2s mark involved in RNA splicing.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "293T were transfected with GFP-RMET, then treated with different compounds for 40h, GFP-TRAP for IP-MS. Samples were run on Thermo 3000 RSLCnano LC and MS on Orbitrap Fusion with 120,000 resolution MS and ion trap MS/MS.",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Charge state deconvolution and deisotoping were not performed. All MS/MS samples were analyzed using Sequest HT (Thermo Fisher Scientific, San Jose, CA, USA; version IseNode in Proteome Discoverer 2.2.0.388). Sequest was set up to search Human_isoforms_051418.fasta; MAxquantcontaminants-042817.fasta (unknown version, 93512 entries) assuming the digestion enzyme trypsin. Sequest was searched with a fragment ion mass tolerance of 0.60 Da and a parent ion tolerance of 10.0 PPM. Carbamidomethyl of cysteine was specified in Sequest as a fixed modification. Met-loss+Acetyl of methionine, oxidation of methionine and acetyl of the n-terminus were specified in Sequest as variable modifications.  CRITERIA FOR PROTEIN IDENTIFICATION-- Scaffold (version Scaffold_5.1.2, Proteome Software Inc., Portland, OR) was used to validate MS/MS based peptide and protein identifications. Peptide identifications were accepted if they could be established at greater than 95.0% probability by the Peptide Prophet algorithm (Keller, A et al Anal. Chem. 2002;74(20):5383-92) with Scaffold delta-mass correction. Protein identifications were accepted if they could be established at greater than 99.0% probability and contained at least 2 identified peptides.  Protein probabilities were assigned by the Protein Prophet algorithm (Nesvizhskii, Al et al Anal. Chem. 2003;75(17):4646-58). Proteins that contained similar peptides and could not be differentiated based on MS/MS analysis alone were grouped to satisfy the principles of parsimony.",
      "projectTags": [],
      "keywords": [
        "Sart3",
        "Hat(half-a-tpr)",
        "Rna splicing",
        "Rme2s reader",
        "Arginine methylation"
      ],
